<P><A CLASS="heading" NAME="tips">email tips</A></P>
<P>
When you are sending an email, you can send it so that the recipient will see your address as your Guildfordians alias.</P>
<P>
To do this in Outlook:</P>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Select <U>T</U>ools, Accounts... from the menu</LI>
<LI>Click on "Add" and then "Mail..."</LI>
<LI>Follow the Wizard, add the same settings as you have already set up for your default account, except enter the email address as your Guildforians alias, ie [title]@grfc.co.uk</LI>
<LI>After you click "Finish", you can then highlight the new account from the list, click "Properties", and change the name to something more memorable</LI>
<LI>When you send an email, instead of clicking on the "Send" button, click on the arrow to the right, and select the name you set up above.</LI>
</UL>
</P>

